<body>
Reports SELECT aliases with names that match column names in the FROM clause.
<p>Example (MySQL):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE TABLE foo (a INT, b INT, c INT);
SELECT a b, c FROM foo;</code></pre>
<p>The <code>a</code> column uses the <code>b</code> alias but the <code>b</code> name is also used by the column from the <code>foo</code>
table.</p>
</body>
